OL,3,GStrathclyde
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FCloudy with rain in the south
OL,6,Fbecoming brighter as showers build
OL,7,Fthrough the morning. These showers
OL,8,Fbecome frequent and merge into longer
OL,9,Fperiods of rain in the north during
OL,10,Fthe afternoon.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FBright spells and showers at
OL,13,Ffirst in the evening but a band of
OL,14,Fcloud and rain soon spreads northeast.
OL,15,FThis becomes heavy at times before
OL,16,Fclearing to showers towards morning.
OL,17,
OL,18,CFriday:FA cloudy start with scattered
OL,19,Fshowers. The showers will decrease as
OL,20,Fbright or sunny spells increase from
OL,21,Flate morning.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
